The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Caparo focus on Tamil Nadu

 OUR SPECIAL CORESPONDENT

 Paul: Constructive

 Chennai, July 29: Caparo Engineering, the UK-based engineering and automobile components manufacturing company, is planning to set up an engineering complex at Sriperumbudur near here. The project is expected to be completed in a year at an estimated cost of Rs 300 crore.

 Talking to reporters after meeting chief minister M. Karunanidhi today, Caparo chairman Angad Paul said the complex would be situated on 128 acres and provide employment to 2,000 people.

 According to Paul, the consolidated engineering complex will house a manufacturing facility, a knowledge-based centre and R amp;D facilities.

 The State Industries Promotion Corporation of Tamil Nadu (Sipcot) has given the land allotment orders to the company. 




